Beat with large spoon until well blended.
Pour into a 9-inch well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll and pinch off marble size. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (do not overbake).

title: homestyle chicken and biscuits
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine gravy and poultry seasoning.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: carla's five can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onions until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup of the cracker crumbs.
Pour in shallow casserole dish.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Combine beans and water in large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to medium and cook 40 minutes.
Add next 8 ingredients; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Mash most of beans against side of Dutch oven with back of a spoon; stir well.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-high and cook, uncovered an additional hour or until desired degree of doneness, stirring occasionally. Discard bay leaves.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: microwave chicken divan
directions: Pierce hole in broccoli package and cook 3 minutes in microwave oven.
In a mixing bowl, mix soup, sour cream, lemon juice, garlic powder and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Put rice and broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole dish and add half of the soup mixture.
Add chicken and remaining soup mixture. Top with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Cover with plastic wrap. Cook 8 minutes. Turn dish 1/2 turn and cook 6 to 8 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together.
Add extra flour if needed.
Roll out; cut into shapes.
Bake for 7 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cook rack of ribs in Dutch oven or regular 350° oven for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.
In a bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake, uncovered, until brown, about 20 minutes.
Keep basting ribs with sauce.

title: onion patties
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Stir in enough cold water for thick batter.
Mix in onion and drop by teaspoons into deep fat.
Flatten patties slightly as you turn them.
Fry to a golden brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops; brown well in skillet, then put in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Turn chops after an hour.
Have a barbecued taste.

title: baked fish
directions: Bake in baking dish covered with foil at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beth's cheese and bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sprinkle bacon over bottom of pastry shell. Combine eggs, cream, salt, nutmeg and cayenne pepper in a bowl and beat until thoroughly mixed. Sprinkle cheese over bacon and ladle egg mixture over top. Bake 15 minutes at 425°, lower the heat to 350° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: cranberry and apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Add the gelatin mixture; chill until thickened. Fold in apples and nuts.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper and onion in margarine.
Combine with tomatoes and steam on low fire.
Mix in soup.
Cook rice according to directions.
Mix rice with tomato-soup mixture.
Add grated cheese and crawfish.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until bubbling.
Don't stir.
Enjoy with salad and French bread. Serves 8.

title: miracle whip-up
directions: Brown and cook the ground beef.
Add the salad dressing, spaghetti sauce, and cooked macaroni.
Heat on medium heat.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread beans on serving platter. Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread over beans. Cover with shredded cheese and sprinkle with remaining ingredients.

title: cheese-pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese and cover pineapple.
Cover this with cracker crumbs. Drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: You will need 2 regular size muffin pans.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Mix garlic, soy sauce, salt and 1/4 cup water.
Add steak.
Marinate steaks 1 hour (longer if possible) tossing occasionally.
Drain steak.
Save the marinade.

title: lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix according to directions on package and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Let cool thoroughly.
Spread with pie filling, then frost with Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated until you serve it.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding over pineapple.
Add other ingredients and stir together.

title: mom's special party cheese balls
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces or grate and allow to come to room temperature.
In mixing bowl, beat cheese and mayonnaise until smooth and creamy.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and parsley.
Continue to beat until thoroughly blended.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts.
May garnish with olives, cherries or parsley.
Freezes well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into margarine mixture with milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased baking dish.
On top of the batter, place peach slices close together.
Pour about 1/4 cup of peach juice over the peaches and batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with milk or ice cream.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, corn and egg in a bowl; mix well.
Place in a casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: spicy hillbilly rice
directions: In a large kettle (4 to 6-quart), place olive oil over heat (medium-low to medium). Add onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic, basil, salt and pepper. Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp. Stir frequently. Add uncooked rice and stir to blend well. Cook for about 2 minutes. Add tomato juice and chili powder. Stir to blend. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover and cook until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired. Serves about 8.

title: southwestern potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Line 2 large baking sheets with foil.

title: crumb crust
directions: Combine crumbs and sugar.
Mix in butter.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan. For unbaked crumb crust, chill 1 hour before filling. For baked crumb crust, bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool thoroughly before filling.
For ease in serving, dip pie pan in warm water for a few seconds, then cut and serve.

title: kraut relish
directions: Mix together and store in closed container in refrigerator. Delicious with vegetables.

title: favorite chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine cranberry sauce, dressing and soup mix in small mixing bowl and mix well. Spread half the cranberry mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange chicken in single layer over prepared layer. Top with remaining cranberry mixture. Bake 30 to 45 minutes until chicken is cooked through. Serve over rice. Yield: 8 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add oleo and mix.
Add other ingredients.
Add vinegar last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: aloha slush
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and divide into 4 separate containers and freeze.
When serving, add 1 quart of 7-up to each container.

title: the best summer cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake mix according to box direction. While slightly warm, poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle and press down flatten cake. Pour crushed pineapple, including juice and spread evenly. Prepare pudding according to box directions, but subtract 1 cup milk. Pour and spread evenly over pineapple. Top with Cool Whip and walnuts. Refrigerate 1 hour prior to serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter then confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Put in greased pan (9 x 13-inch or smaller).
Sets up in 1 hour at room temperature.

title: fresh squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute squash and onions with the margarine until tender. Drain. Add eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and top with cheese and crackers. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: green chili pie
directions: Season meat and onion with salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook until mixture is not pink.
Drain meat.
Place back in skillet. Add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, green chilies and chicken soup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with 6 slices of Armour dried beef. Top with boneless chicken breasts.

title: tiger butter(candy)
directions: Melt vanilla and chocolate almond bark in separate bowls in microwave.
Add peanut butter to almond bark and stir in good. Pour vanilla almond bark mixture in deep cookie sheet (pan must be completely dry).
Swirl in chocolate almond bark.
Let set on counter.
Do not refrigerate!
Cut and serve.

title: polly's sour cream banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in bowl, mixing well after each ingredient is added.
In another bowl, sift together salt, soda, baking powder and flour.
Add alternately with sour cream to first 6 ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in two large loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: teenage scramble
directions: Saute ground beef with onion in oil in skillet until ground beef is browned, stirring frequently.
Add mushrooms and spinach, mixing well.
Stir in eggs gradually.
Cook until eggs are set, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 6 servings.

title: quick fruit crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with a fork.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: chicken soup mother didn't make
directions: Boil chicken, including heart, gizzard and liver for about 45 minutes.
Use enough water to just float the chicken.
Remove pan from heat.
Take chicken out and let it cool.
Save the pot of water.
When chicken is cool, pick the meat off the bones (don't start too early or you will invent words the dog won't stay around to hear).
Put chicken meat back into the pot of water.
Add the complete soup starter, the vegetables for seasoning and the sliced carrots.
Add any leftover veggies found in the fridge.
Cover pot and simmer at least 2 hours.
Serve with cornbread.
It will fix what ails you!

title: my favorite fried potatoes
directions: Fry onions, bacon and mushrooms together, turning frequently until bacon is sufficiently cooked (not crispy).
In a separate frypan, heat vegetable oil on medium-high temperature for 2 to 3 minutes.
Season sliced potatoes with paprika, pepper and salt as listed in large bowl.
Reduce temperature to low-medium; add sliced potatoes slowly to hot oil; turn potatoes frequently.
Fry until light brown color is achieved.
Combine all ingredients in one frypan and cook an extra 10 to 15 minutes and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned water until tender; reserve broth. Debone. Cook potatoes, celery and carrots in broth until tender. Reserve 3 cups broth. Melt butter and flour; stir a few minutes. Add milk, 3 cups chicken broth, salt and pepper. Mix everything together, including peas. Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Shape crusts to fit and put them on top; make a few slits. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Cook the rice following the instructions on the package. This should take about 20 minutes.
Pour the rice into a large bowl to let it cool.
Scramble the eggs in a small pan over medium heat.
chop scrambled chunks of egg into small pea-sized bits with your spatula while cooking.
When the rice is cooled, add the peas, carrots, eggs and onion to the bowl. Carefully toss all of the ingredients together. Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium/high heat.
When the butter has completely melted, dump the rice mixture into the pan and add the soy sauce plus a dash of salt and pepper.
Cook the rice mixture for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring often.

title: stroganoff style pork chops
directions: In a large skillet on medium heat brown pork in oil for 5 minutes.
Remove; keep warm.
In the drippings saute onion and mushrooms until tender, stir in water, mustard and salt; bring to boil.
Return chops to pan; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes, until chops are tender.
Remove and keep warm.
Combine flour and sour cream until smooth; add to skillet.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir 1-2 minutes or until thicken.
Serve pork chops and mushroom sauce with noodles.

title: twice-baked italian cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, butter, anise seed, liqueur, bourbon, almonds and eggs.
Beat to blend. Stir together flour and baking powder. Add to butter mixture and blend thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate dough until firm, 2 to 3 hours.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice on bottom.
Layer chicken, skin side up on rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix water with both cans of soup and heat, then pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove from skillet and set aside. Into bacon drippings stir, vinegar, water, sugar, salt, onion and egg.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add lettuce to skillet and toss with hot dressing quickly.
Remove to bowl.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: chocolate chunk bars
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl; set aside.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind vegetables and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours, then drain. Boil vinegar and spices 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook slowly 30 to 40 minutes.
Seal in hot sterile jars.

title: old-fashioned potato bread
directions: Make potatoes for 2 servings, as label directs, using liquid, omitting butter and seasoning.
Measure 1 cup.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Add 1 cup potatoes, butter and 3 1/2 cups flour.
With electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth, 2 minutes.
Gradually add 4 cups flour, mixing with hands until smooth and stiff enough to leave bowl.
Add remaining 1/4 cup flour, if needed.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth, electric, small blisters appear on surface, 10 minutes.
Place in greased large bowl; turn over.
Cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place (85°), until double, 1 hour.
Turn out dough onto lightly floured pastry cloth or board.
Divide in half.
Roll out one-half into a 16 x 8-inch rectangle; roll up from one end.
Press ends even, pinch to seal and tuck under loaf. Place, seam side down, in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Brush surface lightly with some of the melted butter.
Repeat with other half of dough.
Let loaves rise in warm place, until tops are rounded, 1 hour.
Set oven rack at lowest level.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until deep golden brown and loaves sound hollow when tapped.
If crust becomes too brown, cover with brown paper.
Turn out onto wire racks, brush tops with remaining butter.
Cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: nutty crispies(easy cookies)
directions: Line cookie sheet with sides with foil.
Arrange separated crackers on foil, side by side.
Sprinkle nuts over top of graham crackers.
Bring butter and brown sugar to a boil in small saucepan and pour over crackers evenly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Remove from oven and let set a couple of minutes.
Cut apart with knife while still warm and cool on wax paper.
Makes about 3 dozen 1 1/2 x 3-inch cookies.

title: bohemian turkey soup
directions: Make and brown small meatballs and drain well.
In large stock pot put chicken broth, soup bone and cleaned giblets on medium flame approximately 1 hour.
Remove soup one, skim off and add vegetables.
After another hour, reduce flame.
Add parsley, meatballs and noodles after 10 to 15 minutes, should be ready.

title: cranapple sherbet punch
directions: Mix sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Mix remainder and stir well.
Chill.
Just before serving, add 1/2 gallon pineapple sherbet.
Makes 60 (1/2 cup) servings.
Good for wedding and other receptions.

title: low-fat vegetable soup
directions: Stir onion, cabbage and celery in water.
Simmer until tender. Add rest of the ingredients and simmer.
Serve the next day. (One pound of ground turkey may be added.)

title: five bean casserole
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and onion in sausage drippings until tender.
In large roaster, combine all of the ingredients except bacon.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: goulash
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika, and mustard.
Roll meat in flour mixture.
Brown meat slowly in hot oil.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture over meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Then remove vegetables and bay leaf. Pack meat into jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Cover with sauce, 1 pint 1 hour, 1 quart 1 hour and 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a deep saucepan. When it starts to boil, time it for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, if you desire.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir briskly until it loses its gloss.
Spoon onto wax paper using a tablespoon.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of muffin tin or line with baking cups.
Combine all ingredients except for blueberries. Mix well.
Now add blueberries.
Mix just until blended.
Fill cups and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian cake with chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg whites at high speed with an electric mixer until stiff peak forms.
Set aside.
Beat butter and shortening until creamy; gradually add sugar beating well.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating until blended after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat at low speed until blended after each addition.
Stir in coconut, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8 inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes our clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove cake layers to wire rack and cool completely.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Use wooden spoon to stir up ingredients which are placed into a pot.
Cook until tender.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all and add dressing as much as desired.
There may be too much dressing for this recipe.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix milk and pudding; add to butter mixture and mix well.
Add Cool Whip; mix again.
Crush Oreos; use food processor.
Take a new flowerpot and layer Oreos, then mixture, starting and ending with oreos.
You can use gummy worms in the cake and place silk flowers on top.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon of salt; cut in 1/3 cup butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle cold milk (1 tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface.
Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape into a ball. Chill.

title: snow salad
directions: Drop marshmallows in boiling water, dissolve well.
Add jello and cool.
Add pineapple to cheese and mix well, then add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Add whipped cream and nuts, pour into large pan, 8 x 14-inch, chill well and serve.
May use a large jello mold.

title: diabetic chocolate millionaires
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add quick cooking oatmeal to desired consistency.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Place in freezer to harden.
(This can be rolled into waxed paper and sliced after hardening.)

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend together all ingredients except oil.
Turning blender on low speed, add oil very slowly in a steady stream.
Stir in a few extra seeds.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: white bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook in chicken broth until soft.
Chop onion, celery, cabbage and garlic.
Cook in small amount of oil until soft.
Add to beans.
Add ham, salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place biscuits in pan. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in preheated oven according to package directions.

title: marinated shrimp and artichokes
directions: Chill marinated artichokes and shrimp.
Drain and quarter artichokes and combine with shrimp.
Beat together the olive and vegetable oils, vinegar, mustard, chives, scallions, salt and pepper.
Pour over the shrimp and artichokes.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in food processor.
Set aside.

title: polly smith's pistachio salad
directions: Mix the pudding and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients and blend everything together.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: jello cake
directions: You will need 2 (8-inch) pans and 1 straw or butter knife.

title: texas matador
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions and drain. Brown meat with salt, sugar and pepper in a skillet.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and garlic and cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add the noodles, sour cream, cream cheese and green onions. Place in a casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 people.

title: diabetic yogurt
directions: Completely
dissolve gelatin in boiling water.	Combine cold water
and	enough	ice
cubes
to measure 1 cup.
Add to gelatin and
stir
until	slightly
thickened.
Remove
any unmelted ice.
Stir in yogurt and vanilla.
Pour into individual dishes and chill until set, about 30 minutes.	Makes 2 1/2 cups of 5 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to
Dip chicken into eggs then into bread crumbs and arrange in a 9
by 13 inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes. Take out and pour pasta sauce over chicken and top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: taco burgers
directions: Crush enough corn chips to make 1/3 cup.
Mix ground beef, chips and seasoning mix.
Shape into 6 patties.
Set oven to broil. Broil patties 5 minutes; turn and broil for 3 minutes more. Crisscross cheese strips on each patty and sprinkle with paprika. Broil until cheese is puffed and golden.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook veggies and drain well.
Add chicken, oleo, cheese, soup, salt and pepper.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° (also good with ham instead of chicken and cream of mushroom soup instead of cream of chicken).

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter or oleo in jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle on graham cracker crumbs, nuts, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and coconut.
Pour evenly over top, Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until coconut is brown.

title: tostado dip
directions: Layer refried beans mixed with taco mix.
Layer sour cream with carton of avocado dip.
Layer grated Cheddar cheese.
Layer green onions and black olives.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Spread rice on bottom of oblong dish.
Dissolve bouillon in water and pour over rice.
Place pork chops on rice.
Pour mushroom soup and water over chops.
Sprinkle onion soup over all. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Chicken can be substituted for chops.

title: hedge hogs
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Roll in balls.
Then roll balls in mixture of coconut and confectioners sugar.
Makes about 24 balls.

title: golden potato squares
directions: Saute onion in butter, add milk and bring to boil.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Save 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle on top and bake 30 minutes more.
Cut in squares to serve.
Good with ham and cole slaw.
May be refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: frozen pineapple torte
directions: Beat egg yolks, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add pineapple syrup and lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add pineapple.
Cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ground beef in bottom of glass dish, then pour soup over beef.
Place Tater Tots on top of meat and soup.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Mix together and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Inexpensive and very good for tuna.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir apples and sugar together and let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in remaining ingredients and bake at 375° for 40 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix and drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°. Garnish with pecan halves, if desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: low cholesterol pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Sift baking powder and flour together.
Add to sugar mixture with milk.
Fold in egg whites, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until soft. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together the shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Blend.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: date balls
directions: Cook over low heat first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups Rice Crispies.
Add rest of Rice Crispies if needed.
Prepare aluminum foil with part of coconut; spread over to put mixture on adding more coconut as needed.

title: chess pie
directions: Soften butter; don't melt.
Cream softened butter with sugar; beat well.
Add flour, corn meal and eggs.
Pour in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs (slightly) and combine sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla slowly. Add milk. Mix well. Pour into 9-inch pie pan. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Then in moderate oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and both sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in flour and soda; mix in vanilla.
Roll in small balls.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with glass or refrigerate until firm (overnight) and roll out and cut with cutters.
Color may be added.
Best when soft (before refrigerating).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: artichoke, potato and bacon salad with fennel flowers
directions: Wash and cook potatoes just until tender.
Cut onion lengthways into quarters and cut thinly crosswise.
Soak in cold water.
Cut peppers into strips, 1/4 x 1-inch long.
Cut artichokes in half.
Slice artichokes crosswise in 1/4-inch slices.

title: deep pit(from the oven)
directions: You will need freezer paper and string.

title: hot chicken, shrimp or crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips; put in casserole.
Combine cheese and potato chips and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350 degrees until hot, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Prepare herb stuffing as directed on package.
Set aside. Melt 3 tablespoons butter. Add onion and saute until glassy.
Add soup and cheese, stirring until heated through and cheese is melted. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add the cooked carrots. Turn into greased casserole (2-quart). Cover with stuffing mix.
Drizzle 1/3 cup melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 6.
tags: herb flavored stuffing mix plus rice

title: squash casserole 1
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If bacon drippings are cold, melt them first.
Pour into ungreased dish.
Bake at 350 for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Add egg mixture to the chocolate mixture.
Combine flour, baking powder and nuts in a bowl.
Add to chocolate batter and stir until smooth.
Put in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool and then cut into squares.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press into bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile in a large bowl combine eggs, granulated sugar, baking powder, ReaLemon and remaining 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix well.
Pour over baked crust for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: holiday pecan logs
directions: Butter an 8 inch square pan with 2 tsp. butter, set aside. Combine powdered sugar and dry milk, set aside.
In a heavy saucepan combine 1/2 cup butter, sugar and corn syrup; cook and stir until it comes to a boil and sugar is dissolved.
Stir in powdered sugar, about 1/3 at a time until blended.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Continue stirring until mixture thickens and mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Spread into prepared pan.
Cool.
Cut candy into four strips.
Cut each strip in half.
Shape each strip into a log shape.
Wrap in waxed paper, twist the ends.
Freeze or refrigerate until firm.
In heavy saucepan or microwave melt caramels with milk.
Stir often. Roll logs in caramel mixture then in pecans.
Wrap in waxed paper. Store at room temperature in airtight containers.
Cut into slices with serrated knife.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Cook water and oleo until oleo is melted, then stir in flour; beat well.
Let cool, then add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Spread in cake dish and bake at 350° until golden brown (about 25 minutes).

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine and coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries, sugar and Jell-O just enough to dissolve Jell-O; stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Mix pudding with milk as stated on package.
Add sour cream to pudding.
Fold in 3/4 of Cool Whip.
Layer cake, pudding mix and strawberries in a large dish, repeating until all is used.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: orange-pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer can.
Freeze until firm.

title: sage-onion potatoes
directions: Heat butter and oil in a large heavy skillet.
Add the sliced potatoes; turn them to coat thoroughly in the butter and oil, then cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Turn potatoes often so they cook evenly.
Carefully add 1 cup boiling water to the potatoes in the pan.
Add the scallions, sage, parsley and season with salt and pepper.
Boil, uncovered, for 10 minutes, until water evaporates.
If potatoes aren't done, add 1/3 cup boiling water and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve at once.
Serves 4; 315 calories per serving.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine ground beef, onions and water in saucepan. Simmer until beef turns brown. Add tomatoes, vinegar and seasonings. Cover, simmer 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Fat will float. If time, chill chili and lift off fat layer; if not, spoon off fat.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips. Put in a 13 x 9 casserole dish and top with cheese and chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix syrup, salt, vinegar, salt and pepper and butter in 2 quart pan.
Stir constantly; bring to a boil over medium heat until mixture reaches the hard crack stage 290°.
Add soda and mix well. Pour foamy mixture over corn.

title: deer stew
directions: Cut deer up into small pieces; boil for about 1 hour and a half on medium-high.
Dice onion, potatoes and carrots; add to boiled meat after half hour cooking.
Add all other ingredients and continue cooking for the other hour.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: seven layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter, then pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together dressing, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over other ingredients.
Recipe can easily be doubled.

title: frozen orange dessert
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Set aside 3/4 cup.
Press remaining crumb mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Set aside.
Combine condensed milk and orange juice concentrate. Fold in whipped topping and oranges.
Spoon mixture over crust and sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Cover and freeze until firm. Makes 12 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of oil until golden brown.
Stir in tomatoes and paste; simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in oregano and simmer 30 minutes more.
Mix eggs and salt.
Dip eggplant in eggs; then in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil; drain on paper towels.
Mix cheeses together.
Pour 1 cup mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/3 eggplant and 1/3 cheeses.
Repeat until used up.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly sealed container. Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and roll into two rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from wrap and place on broiler pan; cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili -- quick and easy
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef, onion and pepper in large skillet. Drain off excess grease. Put mixture in a large pot; add chili powder, salt and pepper. Stir in tomatoes and beans. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed ham
directions: Split rolls in half and brush with mixture of butter, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Layer ham and cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for parties.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Chill, then roll into ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, peas and eggs. Sprinkle with bacon.
Ice top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese.

title: rice-con-queso
directions: Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Microwave 1 pound of frozen bacon at Medium-low for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute butter and onion until tender.
Blend in flour. Gradually add chicken broth and cook until it thickens slightly. Stir in wild rice and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry.
Heat to serving temperature.
Add meat and carrots at this time, if desired.
Mushrooms, water chestnuts or chopped bacon may also be added at this time.
Top with sliced almonds, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: This makes a very large salad.

title: our favorite chocolate no-bake cookies(kids' stuff)
directions: Form cake in a dragon cake mold with your favorite cake mix and bake.
Get dry ice; place in small container at mouth of dragon.
Decorate with green icing.

title: pinakbet
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggplant, bitter-melon and okra.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, until beef is tender.
Add eggplant, bitter-melon and okra; cook for 15 minutes.
If using canned bitter-melon, add last 3 minutes of cooking.

title: lemon pepper catfish
directions: Wash fish and place in pan.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with lemon pepper seasoning.
Cover.
Broil for 10 minutes, then turn catfish and repeat process, cooking for another 10 minutes or until fish flakes apart.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces.
Add 2 cans mixed vegetables (Veg-All).
Add 2 cans chicken broth.
Add 1 large can whole tomatoes.
Add large can tomato juice.
Salt to taste.
You can add green beans, peas, carrots or any canned vegetables.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add frozen orange juice, vanilla wafers and nuts. Then roll balls in coconut and put in refrigerator.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Prepare cake mix; let cool. Crush Butterfingers; set aside. Melt margarine in saucepan. Mix in sugar and mix well. Remove from heat. Stir in Cool Whip and mix well. Pinch 1/2 of cooled cake into punch bowl or trifle dish. Pour 1/2 of Cool Whip mixture over cake. Sprinkle layer with 1/2 crushed Butterfingers. Repeat layers and chill.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Serve with egg rolls.

title: joseph's breakfast drink
directions: Blend well. Makes 2 (8-ounce) servings.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: To make this candy, you will first need a large slab of marble on which to pour the hot candy.
Possibly a large cookie sheet would suffice, but I've always used marble.
You will also need several pairs of scissors and at least 3 additional people to help cut the candy before it sets up.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a
large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid, and setting vegetables aside.
In the same kettle, saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add one cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: marsha's dessert
directions: Heat oleo, nuts and flour in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Press down and let cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip on top of cool crust.
Mix puddings with milk and let thicken. Pour over cream cheese topping.
Top with Cool Whip and a few pecans.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Coat cutlets with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter and remove as cooked.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons flour into pan drippings.
(You may have to add more butter to drippings.) Stir in wine, tomato sauce, chicken broth, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat until sauce thickens.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts lengthwise.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.

title: low-fat herbal hash brown potatoes
directions: Steam potatoes over steamer until sticky and not quite done, still hard.
Include garlic, onion and herbs in steamer.
Turn frequently.
For serving 4, you may want to steam a batch of potatoes, set aside and steam the other half with herbs.

title: quick lime icebox pie
directions: Place Cool Whip in bowl and add lemon juice; mix.
Stir in jello and sugar.
Mix well.
May add more sugar, if needed, for personal taste.

title: italian beef
directions: Remove string from around roast and discard.
Place roast in roasting pan.
Pour liquid from jar of peppers over roast.
Remove stems from peppers and discard.
Do not discard seeds.
Chop peppers and sprinkle over roast.
Place in warm oven (200°) before bedtime or in early A.M.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add your soups, milk, enchilada sauce and chopped green peppers to meat and simmer for about 10 minutes. In a greased (Pam spray) pan, add ingredients as below: Layer of meat mixture, layer of crumbled Doritos and layer of grated cheese, repeating layers until all material is used. Bake at 350° in oven for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted. All or parts of the casserole can be frozen.

title: diabetic's cake
directions: Combine applesauce, oil, egg and sugar substitute.
Combine remaining ingredients and add them to applesauce mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until it tests done.

title: italian casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, cook sausage, beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender; drain.
Add tomato sauce and paste, water and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add corn and olives; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in noodles. Pour into two greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes; top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: oriental omelet(from joslin diabetic clinic)
directions: Combine chicken, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and soy sauce and mix well.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, water, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper with a fork.
Heat butter or margarine in a 10-inch skillet.
Pour in egg mixture.

With spatula, draw cooked portions of egg toward center so that uncooked portions flow to bottom. Cook until bottom is set and lightly browned and top is creamy. Arrange chicken mixture on half of omelet.
With spatula, fold other half over and turn out on serving platter.
Yields 2 servings.
Each serving equals 3 ounces of meat and 1 vegetable.

title: date bread
directions: Mix dates, butter, sugar and boiling water and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: magic apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and egg.
Sift together baking powder and flour, then add to sugar mixture.
Toss together nuts and apple, then add to batter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, 3/4 cup cheese, onions and ham together thoroughly.
Now fold in broccoli.
In separate bowl, melt butter and mix in cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Take half of crust mixture and spread over bottom of baking dish.
Pour in soup mixture.
Take remaining crust and smooth over top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake between 375° to 425° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Combine sugar, flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Pour 1 cup buttermilk on top of flour mixture; add yeast to buttermilk and mix slightly.
Add other cup of buttermilk and mix well.
Knead on floured board.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep 1 week.
Take amount needed; roll or cut biscuits.
Dip in melted butter.
Biscuits are lighter if dough is allowed to double in bulk before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and put in greased baking dish.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Turn out onto floured wooden surface.
Knead like bread until no longer sticky.
Add food coloring.

title: easy rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot, not boiling, water, stirring until smooth.
Spread about 1/3 of the melted chocolate in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cover with marshmallows mixed with walnuts.
Pour over remaining chocolate, mixing slightly until marshmallows and walnuts are coated.
Let set until firm.
Cut in squares.
Makes 1 2/3 pounds of candy.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Squeeze excess liquid from spinach.
Place all ingredients in blender-blend till combined.
Butter a souffle dish or 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 to 2 parmesan cheese - pour mixture in and bake at 375 degrees for 50 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: short ribs
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on all sides of short ribs and put into Dutch oven or a 3-quart covered casserole dish.
In a small saucepan, combine the tomato soup with the molasses, vinegar, liquid smoke and minced onion; bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over short ribs; cover and bake in a 275° oven for 3 to 4 hours, or until very tender.
Just before serving, spoon off any excess fat.
(If you prepare this dish ahead, refrigerate it and then lift off the solidified fat before you reheat it.)
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili
directions: Cook all ingredients in skillet for 3 minutes except beans; add beans.
Put in crock-pot and cook until ready or simmer for 25 to 30 minutes atop stove.

title: cumber kimshi(variation of traditional korean cabbage kimshi)
directions: Slice cucumbers very thinly and wilt with salt.
Squeeze out water.
Add spices.
This keeps in the refrigerator for weeks.
It gets hotter the longer it sets.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan at 350°.
Batter will be thick, depending on how juicy the apples are. If too thick to spread, add 1 or 2 tablespoons water.
No other liquid is necessary.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Stir in a lots of love; mix and bake according to directions on box. Serve with lots of hugs and kisses.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make cream sauce of butter, flour, salt, pepper, broth and milk.
This will be thin.
Add chicken and drained peas and carrots.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Make pie crust; roll thin and cut out like biscuits. Place on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Combine all 7 ingredients and mix well (Jell-O pudding mix last).
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche casserole
directions: Place bread evenly into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Set aside. Stir garlic powder into quiche filling. Pour over bread. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Top with pepper rings and bake 5 additional minutes. Let casserole stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together into pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled to serve 16.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Add orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in butter and pour over hot carrots.
Stir to coat.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet cook sausage until well done, drain.
Separate crescent rolls into 8-inch triangles.
Place dough in 12-inch pizza pan, with points toward center.
Press over bottom and sides to form crust.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, stir eggs, milk and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Carefully pour over mixture in crust. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together thoroughly.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together.
Mix together.

title: french cherry delight
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold in sugar, crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Spread in loaf pan (grease well).
Bake 325 degrees for 20 minutes (let completely cool).

title: smothered chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Coat chicken with flour mixture. Melt margarine in heavy skillet. Brown chicken on both sides. Remove from heat. Brown remaining flour mixture in margarine until golden brown, stirring constantly. Slowly stir in water to make gravy. Return chicken to skillet and add onions. Cover and cook on low heat until done, about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: auntie's green bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
This salad will keep for weeks and improves with age.

title: angel cookies
directions: Soak bread crumbs in condensed milk to which the extract and coloring have been added.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Top each with a nut half; bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Decorate top with cherries and crushed cashews

title: cousin susie's perfect fudge
directions: Combine chips and milk and microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 1/2 minutes more.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased glass pan and refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add tomatoes, onion, peppers, cheese and pickle juice.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add celery seed and seasoned peppers to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add eggs and milk, a little at a time, mixing well.
Cook on medium heat, stirring until thick. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: 5 day sour cream cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream and coconut; refrigerate overnight.
Bake cake as directed on package, except use 3 round pans.
Remove from pans; freeze, then slice each layer in half.
Remove filling from refrigerator to soften while slicing cakes.
Spread filling on top of each layer, stacking them.
Refrigerate for 5 days.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Place flour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until caramel colored, stirring flour every 5 minutes. Brown sausage in a Dutch oven or large skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe drippings from Dutch oven.
Brown chicken; drain and pat dry.
Wipe drippings from Dutch oven.
Cook onion, green pepper and celery in Dutch oven (coated with cooking spray) until tender; sprinkle with browned flour.
Gradually stir in water; bring to a boil.
Add sausage (cut into 1/4-inch slices); add chicken, garlic, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, thyme, salt and green onions (optional).
Reduce heat and simmer mixture (uncovered) for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/4 cup butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Mix remaining butter and crushed corn flakes and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into the bottom of a 10 x 13-inch dish the graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick of butter and sugar.

title: green bean relish
directions: Slice beans in thin slivers. Cook 5 minutes. Cool. Cut onions in thin slices. Add beans along with mixture of salad oil, lemon juice, salt, sugar, pepper and paprika. Chill in refrigerator several hours to develop flavor. Serve as salad or relish.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Make graham cracker crust in 9 x 9-inch dish by combining melted margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar. Refrigerate for 30 minutes, until set. Combine microwaved/soft cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix. Add 1/2 tub Cool Whip; mix. Place next to crust. Cover with chocolate pudding. Finish top off with whipped cream. Chill.

title: coconut-orange dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill several hours.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: dorito dip
directions: Brown chopped onions, garlic and salt.
Add drained tomatoes (puncture tomato in strainer to get out most of juice).
Add drained chile peppers.
Cook until all moisture is absorbed, approximately 45 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally. Add cheese.
Stir constantly until melted.
Serve warm with Dorito chips.
Can be cut in half for small gathering.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cream butter.
Blend in sugar and add eggs.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add vanilla and stir in cocoa.
Add flour alternately.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a buttered pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat with flour.
Saute mushrooms and onion in a little oil until onion is clear.
Add beef and brown.
Add tamari and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Use a three or four pound boneless sirloin or rump roast. Boil on stove top until very tender.
Cool and break up into small pieces.
Take out all fatty pieces.
Add enough catsup to moisten well and reheat.
Serve on sandwich buns.

title: chicken crescent casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first 8 ingredients. Cook over medium heat until hot and bubbly.

Place in an 8 x 12-inch ungreased baking dish. Place the refrigerated dinner rolls over hot chicken mixture. Combine the cheese and melted margarine. Spread cheese mixture on rolls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: flaky yellow pastry
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Very gradually add egg/water mixture while gently mixing with fork.
Don't overwork dough.

title: layered salad(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Place lettuce and spinach in the bottom of a large salad bowl. Top with peas, water chestnuts, onion, crumbled bacon and two sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Sprinkle with salt, then pepper as desired.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream, stirring well. Spread mayonnaise mixture over salad to seal tightly.
Sprinkle with cheese, then sugar.
Garnish with remaining 2 hard-boiled egg slices.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla together until stiff.
Add coconut and cornflakes.
Mix until blended.
Drop onto buttered cookie sheet by teaspoons.
Bake at 250° until lightly brown.

title: easy asparagus au gratin
directions: Sauce:
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Slowly stir in 2 cups milk.
When sauce is smooth and hot, reduce heat and stir in cheese.
Season with salt, pepper, Dijon mustard and Worcestershire sauce.

title: veggie burger
directions: Process vegetables in food processor until well chopped.
Mix all with turkey.
Form into burger and bake.

title: chicken primavera
directions: Brown chicken. Remove from skillet and blend soups and paprika.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer hamburger, carrots, onions and potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour tomato soup over this and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Set out 1/2 gallon ice cream to soften.
Roll crackers fine. Melt oleo and combine with crumbs, except a handful saved out for on top.
Pat mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together pudding and milk.
Fold into the ice cream.
Pour over crumb crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Set in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Cut in squares.
Fast and easy.

title: joan's dip
directions: Chop meat and onions (greens only) and mix with cream cheese, soup and sour cream.
Serve with Ritz or Club crackers or with party rye bread.

title: iris' chicken
directions: Place chicken thighs in shallow casserole.
Mix soup with 1/4 cup of water and pour over chicken.
Cover with thin cheese slices, then place Stove Top stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for
1 hour.
Freezes beautifully.
Nice served with asparagus or Chinese pea pods.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine brown sugar and butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan, cutting slices, if necessary.
Place a cherry half, cut side up, in center of each slice.
Sprinkle with reserved juice and then nuts.
Combine cake mix, Dream Whip, right from envelope, eggs and water in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Carefully spoon over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes and then invert onto serving plate.
Let stand 1 minute, then remove pan.
Serve warm or cold.
May also be topped with Cool Whip.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Empty caramels in saucepan with 1/3 cup of milk.
Melt, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup milk, melted butter and nuts.
Press two-thirds of cake mixture in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked mixture. Spread caramel mixture over top of chips.
Add remaining cake mix by spoonfuls on top of caramels.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes. Cut while warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: nacho pizza
directions: Cut tortillas in quarters, making 16 wedges.
Place vegetables evenly on wedges on 2 baking sheets.
Spoon sauce over vegetables and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese starts to brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients and place in airtight container.
To serve, place 1/3 cup mix in cup and add 1 cup boiling water.

title: hamburg casserole with cheesy buttermilk biscuits
directions: Fry hamburg, onion and peppers.
Let cool.
Cook potatoes and celery and add milk and flour; cook until creamy.
Place layer of potatoes, then layer of hamburg, ending with potatoes on top.
Mix biscuit mix (buttermilk kind).
Roll biscuit dough out flat and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut; place on top of potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Remove tamales from can, reserving liquid.
Remove husks from tamales, cut tamales in half crosswise and place in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon reserved liquid over tamales.
Spread chili over tamales, and sprinkle with cheese. Top with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add beef broth.
Cook and simmer. In soup bowls or crocks, place croutons, and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Add soup and top with provolone cheese slices.

title: chicken budapest
directions: Soak raisins in mandarin juice.
Melt butter, brown chicken breasts on both sides.
Cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from skillet, place on serving platter and keep warm.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of pan drippings and stir in flour, paprika, salt and pepper, mix.
Add half and half and cook over low heat until smooth and thick.
Stir in raisin and mandarin juice mixture and heat through.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve over wild rice.
Serves 6.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add potatoes, salt, bacon bits, pepper and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in clams and milk.
Heat.
Do not boil.
Makes 6 servings, about 130 calories each.

title: jamaican fruit cake
directions: Presoak fruit in wine or rum.
Combine fruits and nuts.
Sift flour and mix 2 cups with fruit and nuts. Cream butter until soft and blend with sugar.
Add eggs, singly beating well. Add jelly.

title: greek potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in plastic Ziploc bag and shake to coat evenly.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring several times during baking.
Cover with foil if it browns too fast.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cut strawberries in half to use in cake (save other half for icing).
Mix all the ingredients.
Pour into 2 layer cake pans; bake in 325° oven until done.

title: mama's pineapple salad
directions: Cook beaten egg yolks, pineapple juice, sugar and butter in double boiler until done.
Thicken with flour.
Pour this cooked custard over pineapple, apples and nuts and chill.

title: oriental dish
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Marinate chicken strips in soy sauce, cherry wine and cornstarch for 20 minutes.
Saute chicken in cooking oil until brown.
Add onion, garlic and bell pepper with carrots.
Cook until vegetables turn a bright color. Add broccoli slaw mix, sesame seed and ginger.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 4.

title: camper's cocoa
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container.
Stir in 1/2 to 3/4 cup dry mix into a mug of hot water.

title: hash brown casserole(low-fat version)
directions: Saute onion slightly in Pam-sprayed pan.
Add flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk and broth, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Combine with potatoes and top with cheese and corn flakes, if desired.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch Pam-sprayed pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in square cake pan.
Add rest of ingredients in layer as listed.
Bake at 325° until firm, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in small pieces while still warm.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt, pepper and paprika.
In skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook chicken pieces until well browned.
Sprinkle tarragon over chicken.
Add onion and mushrooms to skillet.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 25 minutes or until tender.
Skim fat from liquid.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and saute with onions and mushrooms.
Add rest of the ingredients and then add sour cream.
Serve over buttered noodles with poppy seed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in corn, eggs, pimentos, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot top with butter.
Add decorative dashes of paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and make a loaf.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: one pot pork chop supper
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops.
Pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix well all ingredients together.
Serve with rye crackers or rye cocktail bread.

title: no crust cheesecake
directions: Beat eggs well in glass bowl.
Fold in sugar and softened cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan (glass) well with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, filling will sink slightly to form its own crust.
Let cool, then cover with your favorite topping (cherry pie filling, berry, etc.).

title: taco dip
directions: Spread ingredients on tray or platter by layers listed.
Top with lots of cheese and arrange olives to look nice.
Use taco chips to dip.

title: long john silver fish batter
directions: Blend beer, flour, butter, egg yolks and seasoning.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Dip cleaned and deveined shrimp or fish into batter. Deep fry at 375 for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: nippy carrots
directions: Use pancake mix and in the place of water in the recipe, use light colored pop (like 7-Up or ginger ale).
It will make the pancakes very light.

title: tiny cinnamon rolls
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 4 rectangles, pinch edges to seal.
Stir together sugar, powdered sugar, and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over rectangles.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion, starting with long side.
Press edges to seal.
Cut each log into 5 slices and place in lightly greased 8 in. round cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over warm cinnamon rolls.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Measure raw rice into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix dry onion soup mix, cream of chicken soup and 1 soup can of water. Arrange pieces of chicken on top (legs, thighs and breasts are good).
Sprinkle chicken generously with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Then, if chicken is tender, let it brown, uncovered, for 15 more minutes.
Watch that the rice mixture stays moist.
You might want to add a little hot water. This is good baked in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan covered tightly with foil.
The paprika gives the chicken color.
Also, there is no salt added as the soups give plenty of flavoring.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with beaten egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: harvest bowl salad
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and lemon juice; cook until thick in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Whip the cream and fold into cooled egg mixture.
Combine fruits, pecans and celery; fold into dressing.
Serves 10.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased 8-inch square dish. Cook at full power for 6 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes of cooking.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: sausage-bread stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, fry the sausage and bacon until crisp and brown.
Remove sausage and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Replace in skillet and add onion, celery, mushrooms, apples, parsley and herbs.
Saute, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Stir in bread cubes and chicken broth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Remove from skillet and place in a bowl.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well and while stirring, gradually add beef bouillon.
Fry bread cubes or croutons in margarine in the skillet.
Combine with onion mixture.

title: strawberry dream pie filling
directions: Mix strawberry halves, jello and yogurt. Add ice cream and mix well. Pour into a prepared light graham cracker pie crust. Place in freezer for at least 4 hours before serving. Let stand at room temperature, 30 minutes before serving. 8 servings per pie. Calories 212.7 and fat 3.05 grams.

title: arlene's appetizer
directions: Cut off top of bread and take out insides.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour mixture inside bread shell. Replace top of bread and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter on low speed. Pour into cookie pie crust. Freeze 3 hours. Top with 1 jar of ice cream fudge topping. Return to freezer. Serve with whipped topping on top of each slice.

title: tangy tuna cocktail
directions: Lightly mix tuna, eggs, pickles and radishes.
In a small bowl, blend mustard, lemon juice, vinegar, salt and cayenne. Gradually stir in salad oil with a fork until dressing is well blended.
Mix dressing lightly with tuna mixture.
If you wish, cover and chill for 30 minutes to 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Mix syrup and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and then stir in the Rice Krispies.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: knox gelatin squares
directions: Mix unflavored gelatin into cold water.
Mix Jell-O into hot water.
Then mix both together.
Pour into Pam sprayed glass 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set until firm.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Mix together very good.
May use in any recipe calling for stuffing.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Stir ingredients by hand until mixed.
Plug in freezer.

title: pasta con presto
directions: Chop
cloves
of
garlic
in
food processor.
While processor
is still running add fresh Parmesan cheese, Italian parsley, pine nuts, fresh basil, salt and vegetable oil.
When mixture is soft and pasty, spoon sauce over freshly cooked hot spaghetti and mix thoroughly.
Add grated Parmesan as topping.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Beat eggs, then add sugar.
While beating, add vanilla and melted margarine.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Makes 12 bars.

title: lemon chiffon pie(makes 8 or 9-inch pie)
directions: Cook in double boiler the egg yolks, sugar, grated rind and juice of lemon and dash of salt, stirring frequently until consistency of thick custard.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add to hot custard.
Mix well.
Cool.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix well and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If desired, cover top with chopped pecans before baking.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating at low speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg, chocolate and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, stirring well.
Stir in pecans or walnuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls, about 1 1/2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes, or until done.
Remove to wire racks.
Frost with Chocolate-Coffee Frosting while still warm.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry angel squares
directions: Cut half of the angel food cake into 1-inch cubes.
Pour boiling water on gelatin in a large bowl; stir until the gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Place cottage cheese in blender container.
Cover and blend on medium speed, stopping blender frequently to scrape sides (about 15 seconds). Return mixture to large bowl.
Stir in pineapple, strawberries and cake cubes.
Pour into square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches). Refrigerate until firm, at least 6 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix softened butter with 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Mix in pecans and form balls, about the size of a round tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and roll in more powdered sugar.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain all beans.
Cook meats and onion in skillet.
Drain. Stir in catsup, mustard and vinegar.
Combine remaining ingredients in 3-quart casserole, stir in meat, cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with bacon if you wish.
Serves 8.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: bubble bread
directions: The night before serving:
Grease a Bundt or tube pan.
Evenly place frozen rolls in bottom of pan; sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Next, sprinkle brown sugar and pecans over rolls, then pour melted margarine over the top.
Place pan in cold oven overnight. As rolls thaw, bread will rise.

title: apple bread
directions: In bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, soda, powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, place oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and apples. Stir flour mixture; add walnuts and mix.
Divide mixture between two greased 8 x 4-inch bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes on rack before removing from pans.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut up sausage into small pieces and cook. Melt cheese, add soup to cheese, stir until well blended.
Cook broccoli. In a seperate bowl mix stuffing, sausage, celery and onions.
Place cut up chicken in bottom of pan, then broccoli, then pour soup and cheese mixture on top. Top with stuffing mixture.
Bake for 40 min. till cheese bubbles and stuffing browns.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Use for dipping apple slices, celery, crackers, etc.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzina
directions: Combine and heat soup, water and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through, stirring, or pour into baking dish and heat in microwave or oven until hot.
Serves 4.

title: spring vegetable dip
directions: Combine mixture together. Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips.

title: garlic steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour; pound to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown steaks in hot oil in a Dutch oven.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add onion to pan drippings; saute until tender.
Return steak to Dutch oven; add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until steak is tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon together. Stir in walnuts and raisins, tossing to coat well with flour mixture.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda. Add to cream mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla; add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 3 (8-inch) pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Beat egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Roll chicken in mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat. Stir in soup, water, onion and seasonings.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: queen victoria's soup(serves 8)
directions: Put the chicken in a large saucepan.
Cover with the stock and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: golden pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in deep fat quickly.
Pour off grease.
Add soup, water, diced celery, pepper and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 30 minutes with lid on pan.
Cook on medium heat on top of stove.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in medium saucepan.
Mix Bisquick and sausage thoroughly, then add melted cheese and mix.
Form into small balls; bake until lightly browned in a 350° oven for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
(Good party recipe.)

title: nothing cake
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 3-quart glass cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream and chocolate or butterscotch sauce.

title: lesueur pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill on bed of lettuce.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla and flour mixture and mix well. Shape in round loaf. Wrap in waxed paper and chill over night. Cut in thin slices and bake in 350 oven.

title: "trailblazer's chili"(serves 10)
directions: In saucepan, heat olive oil.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add meat and cook until done.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes and beef broth.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
The chili will be very thick.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together equal parts of ingredients; keep refrigerated.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry goods in a medium bowl.
Soften shortening in the baking pan or iron skillet in oven at 300°.
Pour into the bowl with the dry goods.
Turn oven to 425°.
Add egg and milk.
Stir. Pour into pan/skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden on top.
(Clabber Girl recipe.)

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Mix together.
Make patties and brown.
Place patties in baking dish.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Beat sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add hot potatoes and beat until smooth.
Add butter, chives, salt and pepper.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Can be made the day before.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, eggs and sugar together.
Add milk, then flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: crock-pot pork chops and stuffing
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing by mixing all ingredients together. Place stuffing in bottom of crock-pot.
Brown and season pork chops to taste.
Place pork chops on top of stuffing.
Cover and cook on low until meat is tender, 2 to 3 hours.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Place blueberry pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix and sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serve topped with whipped topping.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender, not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Cook over low heat. Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons water.
Stir into sauce.
Add shrimp.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: In a bowl, combine cabbage, carrots and green pepper.
Chill. Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, vinegar, Ranch dressing mix, celery seed and salt.
Toss with vegetables.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Freeze.
Spoon 1/2 cup in glass and fill glass with Fresca, Squirt or Wink.

title: caramel corn
directions: Prepare popped corn.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes and stir occasionally.
Remove and add soda. Stir and pour over corn.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 hour.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: glazed onions
directions: Peel onions; cut into even slices.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Add onions and toss for a few minutes until coated with butter.
Do not brown.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and curry powder. Stir to blend.
Add parsley.
Cook onions for about 5 minutes, covered, until almost tender-crisp.
Remove cover and cook onions for 2 to 3 minutes, until glazed.
Season with salt, black pepper and paprika.
Add chili.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Finely chop the first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Better to make ahead and let marinate.
May need to drain off some of the liquid that forms.
Serve with Doritos chips.
Delicious!

title: marinated sliced pickles
directions: In a large bowl, marinate at room temperature for 24 to 30 hours.
Mix occasionally during marinating.
