Then you can store in jars (whatever size you want).
If spices are in cheesecloth, throw them away.
Refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks.

title: picklelets
directions: Beat the egg and sugar until thick and add with the milk to the sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Lastly, add the melted butter.
Mix until smooth and cook in spoonfuls on a hot grease griddle or frying pan.
Serve with butter, jam or sliced strawberries.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve
jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple (with juice).
When
cooled,
add cottage cheese, Eagle Brand and nuts. Stir. Congeal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and sifted dry ingredients.
Add carrots. Stir nuts in last.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: aunt sandy's no-bake cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until they boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and add the other ingredients all at once.
Mix together quickly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let harden.
The secret to this recipe is to work quickly and time carefully.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together (don't beat) and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7-up sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into Ziploc bag; shake to mix.
Add 4 to 6 turkey tenderloins, cut into 2-inch strips.
Marinate for at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
Great on the grill.

title: carrots and walnuts
directions: Cook carrots with water until tender (5 minutes in microwave or 10 to 15 minutes in covered pan over medium heat).
Combine olive oil, nuts, lemon peel and seasoning salt in a bowl.
Add carrots.
Toss.
Serve warm.
Serves 4.

title: bacon and egg bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain fat, reserving 2 tablespoons. Saute onions in bacon fat.
Stir in soup, milk, eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch dish for 20 minutes at 350°. Top with crumbled bacon and serve over muffin halves.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Combine until just moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto bubbling stew, chicken and gravy, etc.
Cover and simmer 12 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in enough water to cover them and cook until tender. Then add tuna, soup and milk. Pour into greased casserole dish. Melt 1/2 stick butter and crumble about 4 slices of bread; mix in the melted butter. Cover top of casserole with mixture. Bake at 400° until done.

title: japanese fried chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients (except chicken).
Add chicken, soak for 20 minutes and deep fry.

title: texas rice
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine the water, uncooked rice, soup mix and onion.
Cover, cook on 100% power (High) for 4 to 5 minutes or until boiling.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, oil, eggs and corn. Mix well. Add peppers and onions. Pour 1/2 mixture into greased 9 x 14-inch baking pan or 10-inch iron skillet. Sprinkle 1/2 of Cheddar cheese; add balance of mixture. Top with remainder of cheese. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cornbread pot pie
directions: Mix meat, peas, corn, cheese, 1 cup milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish or shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until bubbly at edges.
Mix well baking mix, cornmeal, sugar, salt, egg and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour on hot mixture, leaving center uncovered.
Spread to edges.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Brown the Sizzlean on both sides and drain on paper towels. Stir together the dry ingredients.
Stir in the egg, vinegar and water.
Add the bacon.
Cook slowly, stirring until thickened.

title: monster mash potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Cook in boiling water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add next 4 ingredients and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peas and peanut salad
directions: Cook peas.
Drain and cool.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, dill seed, mustard, vinegar and salt until creamy smooth. (I add garlic powder, too.)
Add peas; blend.
Add peanuts.
Best served that same day.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put in large mixing bowl and mix as little as possible. The batter will be a
little chunky.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or microwave.
Stir in nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes approximately 20 to 25 pieces.

title: hot italian submarine sandwiches
directions: Fill sandwich roll with ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and about two tablespoons Italian salad dressing.
Roll in aluminum foil and bake about 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut chocolate cake
directions: Cream eggs and butter in bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 cup of water, beating well after each addition. Stir in sauerkraut. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with favorite frosting.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix until spreadable consistency.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook water, margarine, sugar and Karo until it will spin a fine thread in a glass of cold water.
Add peanuts and cook until light brown (this takes a bit of time, you will start smelling the peanuts cook, then cook a bit longer).

title: lemon dessert
directions: Melt butter; mix crumbs in and press into 9 x 13-inch serving dish.
Dissolve sugar in mixture of lemon juice and rind. Dissolve Jell-O in water and chill in refrigerator.
Whip milk until thick; gradually add Jell-O, beating.
Stir in lemon mixture.
Put in crust and chill.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top for garnish.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Remove lobster from shell.
Cut meat in bite size chunks and reserve.
Make sauce of butter, flour, salt, pepper, milk and evaporated milk.
Cook one minute.
Beat egg yolks and stir in sherry.
Stir in 1 cup sauce into the egg yolk mixture and then add this to the rest of the sauce.
Cook for one minute or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add lobster chunks, scallops and shrimp and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour cake into greased round cake pans covered with wax paper.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: oven-baked apple-pecan pancake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix pancake mix, eggs, water and 1 teaspoon sugar; mix well.
In ovenproof skillet, saute apples in butter until tender.
Remove skillet from heat and sprinkle with nuts. Pour batter evenly over apples.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter.
Cover skillet with lid or foil and bake 12 to 14 minutes or until pancake is puffed and sugar is melted.

title: one dish supper
directions: Fry turkey burger in large skillet.
Bring tomatoes to boil in turkey (cooked).
Add dry rotini to boiling mixture.
Cook about 7 or 8 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with green peas, tossed salad and garlic toast.

title: down south marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt one stick butter and stir in all other ingredients except the marshmallows. Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. After baking, cover the brownies with miniature marshmallows. Put back into oven long enough to melt the marshmallows, but do not let them brown. Cover with icing.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Toss with the Italian dressing which has been made according to package directions.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to cream mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats; drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pistachio cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees: Lightly grease cookie sheets.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring to boiling first 3 ingredients and pour over tea bags. Steam 5 minutes and strain.
Add the remaining ingredients and serve either hot or cold.

title: tuna or salmon dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Mix all other ingredients and serve.

title: orange fruit salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except jello. Then add jello last. Mix well and keep in refrigerator until firm.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 3-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 or 4
additional candies in each cookie, if desired. Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly. Remove to wire rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: "buch'ta"
directions: Warm milk, add yeast and sugar; let melt.
Add the eggs, salt, margarine (melted) and oil.
Add flour and knead dough approximately 20 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken with spicy fruit sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large non-aluminum skillet, bring to a boil.
Add chicken and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from skillet and keep warm.
Bring cooking liquid to a boil; cook 7 minutes or until reduced to 3/4 cup, stirring occasionally.
Combine strawberry spread and cornstarch; stir into cooking liquid and cook 1 minute or until syrupy.
Spoon 3 tablespoons sauce over each chicken breast, garnish with green onion strips.
Yields 4 servings, 215 calories and 1.5 fat.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together in bowl; set aside.
In saucepan melt butter; add cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to a boil; boil one minute.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix buttermilk and soda and add. Add eggs and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Last, stir in marshmallows.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 13-inch); bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and blend well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Melt cheese and oleo; mix in half and half, all in pan.
Pour over potatoes and let stand for an hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy garden caesar dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a food processor or blender and process until smooth. Serve the dip in a shallow bowl or small hollowed out bell pepper.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: ranch house casserole
directions: Melt shortening in skillet over medium heat.
Place meat in skillet and scramble it.
Let it cook until done but not brown. Add all other ingredients and turn heat to low; heat and let it simmer until hot.

title: sausage treats
directions: Mix all together well. Make into very small biscuits.
Cook on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken soup with matzo balls
directions: Place chicken, water, onions, leek, celery, salt and pepper in 8 to 10-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and parsnips; simmer covered for 30 more minutes.
Remove chicken and refrigerate if you are not planning to use as main meal.
Lift vegetables from broth with slotted spoon, then strain broth. Return vegetables to broth.
Add parsley and dill if desired. Heat through and serve in bowls with Matzo Balls.
Serves 15.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruit, nuts and sour cream.
Fold in cool whip and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.
Yields 10-12.

title: finger jello
directions: Put unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Mix.
Put flavored gelatin in large bowl and add boiling water.
Add plain gelatin to flavored gelatin.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate to set (20 minutes).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Bring 6 cups water to boil.
Add salt and macaroni; cook until tender.
Grate cheese coarsely, then put in large baking dish, layering alternately with cooked macaroni.
Beat eggs in milk; pour over this mixture.
Take fork; mix well, down through pie. Bake at 400° or 450° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Black pepper is optional.

title: italian love cake
directions: Grease and flour 11 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake according to box directions; pour into pan.
Mix vanilla, sugar, eggs and cheese. Pour gently over cake mix.
Do not blend.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Layer chiles, cheese, meat and chiles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together flour, salt, eggs, milk and hot pepper sauce.
Pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks and margarine.
Cook until it bubbles good and gets thick. Let cool.
Add 3 cups of sliced strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: overnight tuna casserole
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Whisk soup and milk in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except reserved cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until red disappears.
Add garlic, onion salt, chicken gumbo and catsup.
Simmer for 2 hours.
The longer it simmers, the tastier it gets.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add to cooled jello and chill.

title: velvety cocoa frosting
directions: In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat confectioners sugar, cocoa, butter, water, vanilla and egg yolk until smooth, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.

title: cherry christmas cake
directions: Beat butter until softened and light.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition. Stir in almond flavor.
Mix flour and salt together.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk (about 1/3 each time).
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake in greased tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: charlotte russe(basic recipe)
directions: In a double boiler, beat the egg yolks and add 2 tablespoons sugar gradually while beating.
Add salt and milk.
Cook over hot water until mixture coats the spoon, stirring constantly.
Soften gelatin in cold water; add to hot custard and stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold in.
Whip the cream; add remaining 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla extract. Fold in.
Line sherbet glasses or spring-form mold with the ladyfingers and fill with the custard.
Chill until firm.

title: minted lime mold salad(yield:  6 servings)
directions: Heat 1 cup water and limeade concentrate to boiling.
Pour over gelatin in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water, ginger ale and peppermint extract.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in pears and melon balls.
Pour into 7 cup jello mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce and garnish with extra cantaloupe balls and mint sprigs.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook chicken.
Chop when cooled.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar together.
Gradually add oil; add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Gradually add flour mixture to first mixture (will be thick).
Fold in apples.
Add 1 cup nuts or raisins.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Use greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: poppy seed orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat all ingredients at low speed, scraping bowl often, until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into greased tin.
Bake 17 to 22 minutes.

title: delicious and healthy pancakes
directions: Preheat frypan or griddle.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and skim milk; stir just until combined.
Fold in egg white gently; add olive or salad oil.
Cook on hot griddle which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
These pancakes contain no cholesterol.

title: spinach dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Stir before serving. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and sour cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and baking soda which have been sifted together.
Add flavoring.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done in center.

title: sausage roll-ups snacks
directions: Cut smokey links lengthwise halfway through.
Insert long thin wedge of dill pickle (drained) in each cut.
Spread triangle of dough of crescent roll as label directs.
Lightly spread each triangle with cheese.
Place smokey link, pickle side down, on wide end of triangle and roll up toward point.
Repeat with each roll and link.
Arrange rolls on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush with melted butter or margarine and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge topping for ice cream
directions: Boil chocolate and milk until thick, about 3 minutes.
Add sugar, butter and marshmallows.
Add vanilla.

title: japanese fruitcake pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar and eggs together (after butter has cooled to
room temperature).
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients
and pour evenly into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mash beans with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended, refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gingersnap crust
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gingersnaps and sugar.
Press evenly into the bottom of an oiled, 9-inch spring-form pan and freeze until needed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire together.
Form one ball and roll in chopped ham.
Serve with crackers.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Stir jello into cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.
I sometimes use 3 ounce size fruit cocktail in place of oranges and pineapple.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Mix in next 8 ingredients.
Stir in 3 cups cooked noodles.
Top with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream together oil, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour, baking soda and powder.
Mix in oatmeal, Post Toasties, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Put 6 scoops on each cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop.
Heat oven to 350°. Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease or spray Pam on large square pan or dish.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture in pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix melted caramels, margarine and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over cake that's baked.
Pour remaining cake batter over mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: butterscotch pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Let cool.
Add cake mix. Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 pan.
Add butterscotch morsels on top of cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: parmesan dip
directions: In a small bowl with fork or wire whisk, mix mayo, anchovy fillets, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice and black pepper.

title: lemon-butter broiled chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken quarters on both sides with salt and pepper. Melt butter in small saucepan; add lemon juice, tarragon, chervil and vermouth; brush part over chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, on rack of broiler.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 20 minutes, basting frequently.
Turn; broil 15 to 20 minutes longer or until nicely browned, brushing with remaining lemon-butter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roasted salted pecans
directions: Toss pecans in bowl with oil until well coated.
Spread on cookie sheet; salt to taste.
Cook at 400° for about 10 minutes. Check; should be a little brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
Pack into containers.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Prepare Duncan Hines angel food cake mix according to directions on box.
Let cool.
Break into bite size pieces.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with pieces.
Prepare 1 package chocolate pudding mix according to directions.
As it begins to boil, stir in 1 package chocolate bits.
Cool slightly.
Fold in 1 carton Cool Whip.
Pour over angel food cake bits.
Ice with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Put pecan bits on top.

title: asian beef stew
directions: Heat wok over high heat 1 minute.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon oil into wok.
Heat 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 of beef and stir-fry about 5 minutes until brown.
Repeat with remaining beef.
Remove beef to bowl; set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to wok.
On medium heat, add shallots.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove to same bowl.
Repeat same for onion and garlic.
Return all beef and juices to wok; add water, sugar, salt, anise seed, cinnamon, pepper and bay leaves. Reduce heat; cover 1 1/4 hours until meat is done.
Peel carrots and turnips; cut into 8 wedges.
Add carrots, turnips, shallots and lemon peel to beef.
Cook until tender, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf and lemon peel.
Stir in tomato paste.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens, then serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each separately until done. Season with salt. Drain well.

title: andes candies cookies
directions: In small saucepan, combine margarine, sugar and water until sugar has dissolved.
Add chocolate chips till partially melted. Remove from heat and stir until chips are totally dissolved and mixture is smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put pecans in bottom of cake pan; spread cake mix over pecans.
Melt stick of margarine; mix with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub each potato; dry with a paper towel.
Cut each potato into eight wedges; arrange peel side down in a shallow baking pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden and tender.
Brush occasionally with mixture.

title: rice medley
directions: Add enough water to reserved vegetable liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Pour into 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in peas, rice, butter, salt and carrot.
Heat to boiling. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: pan fried liver
directions: You will need an iron frying
pan.

title: thin mint girl scout cookie dessert
directions: Mix pudding and 2 cups of milk until smooth.
Add chocolate Cool Whip; set aside.
Crumble 1 box of thin mints in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Pour in half of the pudding mixture.
Top with vanilla Cool Whip.
Continue to layer, saving 1/4 cup of cookie crumbs for top.
I use a Tupperware container so I have the cover to store in the refrigerator overnight.

title: cheese and chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce and cream cheese; cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in 1 cup cheese.

title: glaze for fresh fruit pie
directions: Mix and boil one minute.
Pour over fresh strawberries or peaches in baked pie shell.

title: potato soup(microwave)
directions: Combine potatoes, onions and water in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish. Cook, covered, on full power, 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir one time. Lightly mash potatoes. Stir in flour. Add milk, salt and pepper. Cover and cook on full power 5 minutes longer, stirring every minute or until soup boils and is thickened.

title: miracle brownies
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces; place in bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Brown flour with butter; gradually add beef consomme soup.
Add mustard, sour cream and catsup.
Bring to a boil.
Set sauce to one side.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in vegetable oil.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Thinly roll out dough (1/4-inch thick) on a lightly floured board into two 10 x 18-inch rectangles.
Spread on sausage; roll up lengthwise.
Chill well and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine crushed pineapple and its juice and 1 cup sugar.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Punch holes in cake and pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Let cool.
Prepare vanilla instant pudding.
Pour over cool cake.
Slice 3 bananas and layer over pudding.
Spread with 8 once carton Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken as for frying, place with seasonings in a large kettle with enough cold water to cover.
Bring slowly to a boil, simmer until meat comes off bones.
Remove bones, cut chicken in fairly large 1/2-inch pieces.
Return to pot; add onions, potatoes and butter beans.
Cook until done; add tomatoes and corn, cut from cob.
Cook slowly for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: prune bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, cooking oil and prune baby food well and add other ingredients.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In a large skillet combine chicken and 1/3 cup Italian dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta or mix pasta with vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese. Yields 5 servings.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix all together and put in muffin tins. Sprinkle pumpkin seed on top. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: conga bar
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar.
Stir and let cool.
Add eggs (one by one), flour and vanilla.
Stir.
Add peanuts and chocolate chips.
Stir again.
Pour mix in greased rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan full of apple slices. (Spray pan with vegetable spray first).
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of cinnamon and sugar.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, honey and salt together.
Add milk gradually.
Add beaten eggs and butter.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add blueberries, sprinkled with flour.

title: 6 layer mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order.

title: ms. carly's broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Spread cooked broccoli in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chicken, salt and pepper lightly.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Top with corn flakes and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Prepare jello using pineapple juice for cold water.
After thickened, add other ingredients.

title: strawberry pretzel salad #2
directions: Mix together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes in 400° oven.
Set aside to cool.

title: fruit ice
directions: Mix above ingredients in blender.
Serve in glasses and enjoy; it tastes like ice cream without the fat!

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Combine French dressing, mayonnaise, salt and pepper to make dressing.

title: anise cookies
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until thick; add sugar gradually. Continue beating until sugar is dissolved.
Add anise and beat until thoroughly blended.
Beat in flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Chill dough for several hours or overnight; roll into a rectangular sheet 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut cookies in 1 1/2-inch squares; place on greased baking sheet and chill, uncovered, for about 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool and store in covered container.
These can keep for weeks. Makes 60 cookies.

title: simple shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on floured board (1/4 to 1/2-inch thick).
Cut into desired shapes and arrange on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 3 layers.
In the bottom of the punch bowl, put the strawberry pie filling.
Add a layer of cake.
Mix pudding according to package directions and add drained pineapple.
Spread on top of cake layer, then add second cake layer.
Top this layer with cherry pie filling and add third layer of cake.
Mix second box of pudding as directed and add 3 bananas, sliced.
Spread on top of third cake layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.

title: none such mincemeat prize cookies
directions: Cream together until fluffy the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat
until smooth.
Stir together the flour, soda and salt. Add to first mixture.
Stir crumbled mincemeat into dough.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart by rounded teaspoonfuls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.
A tasty, mild, fruity cookie.

title: reuben-wich
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large warm bowl.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and 2 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough more flour to make soft dough.
Knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Punch dough down; divide in half.
Roll half to 14 x 10-inch, spread half dressing down center third of dough length.
Layer with half the beef, cheese and sauerkraut. Make cuts from filling to dough edges along sides of filling, 1 inch apart.
Alternating sides, fold strips at an angle across filling; place on greased baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Brush with egg, sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers; reheat to serve. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheesecake factory key lime cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir to coat well the ingredients. Keep it crumbly.
Press crumbs on bottom and half way up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter or margarine and eggs; mix well. Sift flour and then measure out three cups; add soda and salt and sift again.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture a little at a time letting your batter blend well between each addition.
Add in bananas and nuts and mix well.
Pour into well greased tube or Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 13 x 9-inch dish, except Ritz crackers and melted oleo.
Roll Ritz crackers to crumbs; toss with stick of melted butter.
Top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown on top (20 to 30 minutes).

title: quick and easy rice jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add sausage; cook and stir until lightly browned. Add chicken, onion, pepper, celery and garlic; cook and stir until chicken is cooked through. Stir in tomatoes, okra, tomato sauce and seasoning. Bring to boil. Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Stir.

title: ruth's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shake well.
Serve over spinach salad.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put in small cake pan in layers:
Bean dip, guacamole (avocados mixed with the mayonnaise), sour cream mixed with taco seasoning, shredded cheese, tomatoes, olives, onions and shredded cheese. Serve with chips.

title: irish kisses
directions: Beat up the butter and all the other ingredients.
Sift in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop a teaspoonful at a time on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar.
Bake in hot oven.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add all ingredients and blend well.
Drop with teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: easy jello salad
directions: * Do not add water.

title: savory upside-down pie
directions: Thaw pastry.
Mix ground beef, salt, pepper and onion; bind with egg yolks.
Wash and quarter mushrooms.
Cover the bottom of an 8-inch loose bottomed cake pan with the bacon.
Arrange the cheese, herbs and mushroom quarters on top.
Cover the meat mixture, pressing it down firmly and smoothly on the top.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Make a well in dry ingredients and add egg, vinegar and cold water.
Prepare as for any pie crust.
